==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unked
<hw>Un"ked</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Corrupted fr.
<ets>uncouth</ets>, or OE. <ets>unkid</ets>; <ets>un-</ets> + p. p. of
AS. <ets>c⟦ymac⟧⟦edh⟧an</ets> to make known, fr. <ets>c⟦umac⟧⟦edh⟧</ets>
known. See <er>Uncouth</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Odd; strange; ugly;
old; uncouth.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Lonely; dreary; unkard.</def> <mark>[Prov.
Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Weston is sadly <qex>unked</qex> without you.</q>
<rj><qau>Cowper.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unkemmed</ent>⟦br⟧
